$ System.Runtime.InteropServices.CharSet (enum)

The `System.Runtime.InteropServices.CharSet` enum specifies the → development/Unicode/character-set with which strings are marshalled and is used by
the → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Runtime/InteropServices/DllImportAttribute[`System.Runtime.InteropServices.DllImportAttribute`] and
→ Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Runtime/InteropServices/StructLayoutAttribute[`System.Runtime.InteropServices.StructLayoutAttribute`]

Members in this enum are:
table { lrl
  `Ansi` ☰ 2 ☰ Multiple-byte character strings: the system default Windows (ANSI) code page on Windows, and → development/Unicode/UTF-8 on Unix.
  `Auto` ☰ 4 ☰ Marshal strings accoring to the target OS, languages may override this default: → development/languages/C-Sharp and Visual basic will use `Ansi`
  `None` ☰ 1 ☰ *Obsolete*, now same as `Ansi`
  `Unicode` ☰ 3 ☰ 2-byte characters
table }

